Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @Brussels sprouts{500%grams} and halve through the root.

Place a #pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{1%tbsp}.

Fry sprouts and @Irish bacon lardons{100%grams} until starting to brown, ~{3-4%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Meanwhile, combine the @grated Italian style hard cheese{2%units} and @breadcrumbs{1%pack} in a #bowl then season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Add 1 tbsp oil and mix until well combined.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} to the sprouts and cover the pan with a #lid.

Cook until sprouts are tender, ~{4-5%mins}.

Add @flour{1%tbsp} and mix well.

Stir in @creme fraiche{110%grams}, @chicken stock{1%sachet} and @water{100%ml}.

Bring to a boil until you reach the consistency of a bechamel. Add a splash of water if the sauce becomes too thick.

Transfer to an #oven dish{} and sprinkle over the cheesy breadcrumbs.

Pop onto the top shelf of the oven and bake until golden, ~{10-15%mins}.

Remove from the oven and set aside to cool before serving, ~{10-20%mins}.